(iii) more preferably a melting point in the range of 45 (degree)  C. to 53 (degree)  C. and a refractive index in the range of 1.445 to 1.453; and


(iv) most preferably a melting point in the range of 47 (degree)  C. to 53 (degree)  C. and a refractive index in the range of 1.451 to 1.453;

Such co-additives include the following:


(i) ethylene-unsaturated ester copolymers;


(ii) comb polymers;


(iii) hydrocarbon polymers;


(iv) sulphur carboxy compounds;


(v) polar nitrogen compounds;


(vi) hydrocarboxylated aromatics;


(vii) polyoxyalkylene compounds.

